transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: My name is David Sebastian.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: And I'd like to...

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Mr. David Sebastian, how can I help you, sir?

Speaker 1: I'd like to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 2: You just don't need to refill your prescription?

Speaker 1: Would you like to order as needed so we can stop if you don't need to month it?

Speaker 2: Because I see you just had to refill, so you prefer to order yourself as needed?

Speaker 1: I just want to...

Speaker 2: I wasn't aware that I was going to be charged monthly and need it monthly.

Speaker 1: I mean, you don't have to get it.

Speaker 2: That was the initial prescription from Dr. Tariq because you ordered 10, and it was 30 days in the month.

Speaker 1: So the doctor is assuming that you're active.

Speaker 2: But when you're not, when you called, we're understanding right away that, you know, you probably don't need your refill.

Speaker 1: So we tell the pharmacy to pause everything so you can just order as needed because obviously it's not necessary.

Speaker 2: No, well, look, they've already charged...

Speaker 1: Listen to me.

Speaker 2: Hold on a minute.

Speaker 1: They've already charged me for another refill.

Speaker 2: A refill, yeah.

Speaker 1: And I did not order that.

Speaker 2: Yes, and I was saying, do you want me to stop them the monthly so you can order yourself and don't get charged on the monthly?

Speaker 1: But you're just going to order as needed?

Speaker 2: I'm going to order as needed, yes.

Speaker 1: Yes, so that's what I'm offering because I understood your concern.

Speaker 2: You know what I mean?

Speaker 1: Well, you know, it's really not working that well anyway.

Speaker 2: And actually, I would just as soon just, you know, stop the subscription altogether.

Speaker 1: That's your first time taking Viagra?

Speaker 2: No, I've taken it before.

Speaker 1: A while ago before that new prescription?

Speaker 2: Look, I just want to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Can I do that?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: I apologize to ask you a question.

Speaker 2: We try to assess to help patients understand what is the issue.

Speaker 1: I apologize to ask you a question.

Speaker 2: So I'm canceling everything.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: You're good to go.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: You all set.

Speaker 1: I'll cancel your account and everything.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And that's all I need to do.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: No, that's all.

Speaker 1: You have a good one.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
